<br>
Anyone interested in hunting in PoG? Sign up or just show up. <br>
<br>
When: Thursday, April 10th. 5pm - 9pm CST.<br>
<br>
Target: Anything and everything, depending on how many people we get. Note: you can do most of the zone with a single group, but we'll be able to kill them quicker and easier the more people we have, which means better odds at armor drops and if we clear enough of the zone, we can do some of the bigger guys if we have the force.<br>
<br>
Reason: Fun and profit. Nothing more fun than killing Tunare's minions and they drop armor equivalent to Thurgadin quest armor. Mainly doing it to get to know some more people and to give the people who aren't able to go there with thier friends or guild because of faction issues the chance to hunt in the zone and get some decent gear.<br>
<br>
Loot: On gear and spells, if you can and will use, you'll /ran 1 - 1000 with whoever else can and will use the item. If noone can and will use the item, everyone can just roll to sell or give to friends. On gem drops, I or someone else can master loot them and at 9pm, when the raid is over, we'll all /ran 1 1000 and whoever ends up with the largest number gets all the gems. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (cash drops will be used to reimburse the clerics or the like.)<br>
<br>
As long as we get a shaman, tank, and a cleric, we'll be good. I'd rather not have more than 2 or 3 groups because it would be overkill unless we're gonna be brave and try Tunare herself or the like, but I don't see that happening. :P<br>
<br>
Btw, I expect you to at least know how to /assist the Main Assist, manage your agro, etc., but I will explain anything zone/mob-specific at the raid. I also won't be responsible for you screwing your faction up if you need it for some reason (druid/ranj0r/pal epic)... :P<br>
<br>
